            "text": "Procedure involved removal of the prosthesis and cement from the proximal femur and insertion of a modular endoprosthesis (LPS ® DePuy Limb Preservation System (Warsaw, IN, USA) proximal femoral replacement). The acetabular component was also revised. A trochanteric claw plate was used to re-attach the bone of the proximal femur to the prosthesis to ensure good abductor function."
