            "attachment": {
              "contentType": "text/plain",
              "data": "The patient underwent a both component revision arthroplasty procedure for a Vancouver B3 peri-prosthetic fracture of the right hip. She tolerated the surgery well and was able to commence immediate full weight-bearing, protected with a Zimmer frame, on postoperative day one. At her six-week postoperative evaluation, she was ambulating independently, though continued with the use of her walking frame for ‘balance and confidence’. She was discharged with stable vital signs and overall good health."
